title: His Ma'ties speech, [brace] & [brace] the Queenes speech
author: England and Wales. Sovereign (1625-1649 : Charles I)
notes: Includes: The reasons of the House of Commons, to stay the Queenes going into Holland / delivered to the Lords, at a conference the 14. of July, by John Pym Esquire ; and delivered the 15. to His Majestie, in presence of both Houses, by my Lord Bankes.
